    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-16T07:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-16T07:00:00-05:00" n="249"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d249">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 E.W. 1939/9–1644: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harriman</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-16T15:00:00+03:00"
                            >September 16, 1944—3 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 16—11:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3533. ReDeptel 2206, September 14, 9 p.m.<note n="31" xml:id="d249fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> Vyshinski,<note n="32" xml:id="d249fn2">Andrey Yanuaryevieh
                        Vyshinsky, Assistant People’s Commissar for Foreign Affairs of the Soviet
                        Union.</note> the British Ambassador and I yesterday signed on behalf of our
                    respective <pb facs="0248" n="238" xml:id="pg_238"/> Governments the protocol to
                    the Rumanian Armistice proposed by the British. In addition to the two points
                    reported in my 3423 of September 11, 2 p.m.,<note n="32a" xml:id="d249fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_230">p. 230</ref>.</note> it
                    contains a definition of war material, reading, paraphrased, as follows: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“In Article VII the term ‘material’ shall be deemed to include all
                            equipment or material belonging to, used by, or intended for use by,
                            enemy military or para-military formations or members thereof.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>The protocol is in the alternate form and is dated September 12 to coincide with
                    the date of the armistice. It will not be published.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harriman</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
